        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=2567&FORUM_ID=60&CAT_ID=11&Forum_Title=NWN+General+Discussion+%2D+Public+Access&Topic_Title=%22The+Word%22+on+NWN+%2D+I+was+there%2E%2E%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Last year, I was at E3 and viewed NWN in action, real time... and loved it. I was one of maybe 200 people allowed access into the room - closed door - to see the game and ask all questions.</P><P>As a DM from 1983 to 1993, I can say with certainty that I asked every conceivable question I could think of. So if you have a specific question, ask it here - and I will give you an answer if I have one. If I cannot answer it, we can hit the NWN forums.</P><P>Things I know:</P><P>1: LOA *WILL* have our own server for NWN, matter of fact, I already have it worked out with our lostorder.com provider. We have TONS of bandwidth, and a reliable server that will host this for us.</P><P>2: You can link 'modules' together with other modules. So Stubby may create the "outdoor" module for LOA. Heading to Dungeon A will spawn a module created by Brimstone. Within that Dungeon may be a link to the Etherial Plane, created by Solf.</P><P>3: You can configure the SERVER and MODULES independently. Such as:  # of characters in-game at any given time; twinked characters allowed: yes/no (I can explain how they determine who is twinked or now); custom items allowed: yes/no; etc. There are a million variations that give the DM / Server Host the choices we want. Modules ALSO contain the ability to specify a million options that the DM makes the decision on. So the server is ONE layer of 'choices', while the MODULE may (or may not) have another layer of rules/choices.</P><P>4: The game comes with a huge list of armor, weapon, magic item, artifact, etc. based on actual AD&D guides. In addition to that, THE DM CAN MAKE brand new items, with all the bells and whistles. Name the item, set spells it has, curses, + to hit, + damage, etc. You name it, they thought of it.</P><P>5: Currently up to 64 people in game at any given time, last I heard. That # is determined by the DM - and is set IN the module.</P><P>6: DMs can enter ANY "NPC" and control them, further adding to the fun in a campaign. DMs can be an "ACTIVE" NPC, or can simply "SPY" from the NPCs point of view.</P><P>---</P><P>I know a bunch of other stuff, too. I have the official press release from 2001 here. I also have the business card for the lead developer.</P><P>Ask away...</P><P>Brimstone</P><P></font></td>

