		<a name="10912"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/12/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 06:17:30</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=11"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=ICQ&ICQ=2394483&M_NAME=Gooba')"><img src="http://online.mirabilis.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=2394483&img=5" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Gooba an ICQ Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=10912&TOPIC_ID=2567&FORUM_ID=60&CAT_ID=11&Forum_Title=NWN+General+Discussion+%2D+Public+Access&Topic_Title=%22The+Word%22+on+NWN+%2D+I+was+there%2E%2E%2E&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Questions:</P><P>1. Does a DM need to be present for players to participate in his scenario?</P><P><b>Brim:  Nope, not at all. That is optional.</b></P><P>2. On a related note, does a created scenario "refresh" itself after characters go in and wipe it out?  If so, what is to prevent characters from repeating a scenario several times to get a magic item that all of them shouldn't have?</P><P><b>Brim:  I am pretty sure (and will recheck) that you can configure your module to check each character to see if they have already finished the module. If they have, they can be turned away from going through again.</b></P><P>3. Can anyone be a DM, or just those specified by the server?</P><P><b>Brim:  ANYONE can be a DM and create modules, items, NPCs and more. DMs can then play their modules on their computer, OR use their computer as a server if their connection is good (like Tribes, Quake, etc.). However, if you want to have YOUR module on the LOSTORDER.COM box, you will have to go through those who have access (i.e. Brimstone, initially... until we sort out the rules, process, etc.). A module created by ONE DM, can only be DMd by another person if they own the module and host it on their own server OR if the DM OPTION is enabled for others to use. Confused? DM ability is an option turned on or off.</b></P><P>4. Can any DM enter the persona of an NPC created by another DM?</P><P><b>Brim:  NOPE. Not by default.</b></P><P>5. How cooperative will our DM's have to be all on the same server?  Will they need to work together often?</P><P><b>Brim:  Not at all. Our server will have lots of modules (eventually). We can choose to keep them seperate 'campaigns', or we can choose to link them together.  Our choice. DMs CAN choose to work together, which I think is really wonderful.</b></P><P>6. Can multiple DM's run a scenario simultaneously?</P><P><b>Brim:  I believe so, but I will find out for sure.</b></P><P>7. Does our server have an "overseer" who coordinates everything?</P><P><b>Brim:  We will have an admin who ensures that things on the server are accurate, working and cared for. The gameplay is self-sufficient and doesn't require a person to oversee anything.</b></P><P>8. Is NWN the kind of game, like DAoC or EQ, where people are logged in all the time, or will we have to arrange set times to group and hit the dungeons?</P><P><b>Brim:  Yes and no. If the module permits, people can log in at any time and become a part of the world. 1 person, or eventually 64... the module and server will go by the 'rules/options' set by the admin and DM.  For more fun, we SHOULD set a time for our members to meet in-game and play a certain module together. ALSO... and this is cool, you can set modules to "PVP Enabled". So 8 people can login and be "Team A" while another set of people login and become "Team B". They can then PK each other...</P><P>Perhaps, one module is for TEAM A and another seperate module is for TEAM B. Small module. Both lead to a center area - dungeon/arena/etc. that is PK-Enabled. Allowing both sides to duke it out.</b></P><P>9. Can this be run in windowed mode, so we have access to chat <BR>clients like IRC, or is there a chat area inside the game?</P><P><b>Brim:  At E3, yes... it was windowed. Not sure if it will be when it goes gold.</b></P><P>That's all I can think of for now.</P><P><b>Brim:  Thanks!</b></P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

