        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> 1. Does a DM need to be present for players to participate in his scenario?</P><P>No DM's don't have to be present although the more active the gm is, the more interesting he can make a premade scenario or alter the events. Do you remember how alive the BG cities were with talking, reacting npcs? Well the tools are supposed to be there to create the exact same npc interaction. Not to mention there is an entire single player game that can be loaded up into the game editor to give DM's an idea of exactly how they can accomplish that same hands-off module creation.</P><P>2. On a related note, does a created scenario "refresh" itself after characters go in and wipe it out? If so, what is to prevent characters from repeating a scenario several times to get a magic item that all of them shouldn't have?</P><P>The developers have said they made the game in the tradition of D&D and once a moster or npc is killed its go forever, same with pickep up items. There will be options to make continually respawning mobs/encounters for those interested in a "persistant" type world where they can kill thing over and over to level. Anyway thats a good question, hopefully there is a way to stop a person from learning how an encouter works and repeatedly doing it to farm gold and items.</P><P>3. Can anyone be a DM, or just those specified by the server?</P><P>Need permission and a password to DM</P><P>4. Can any DM enter the persona of an NPC created by another DM?</P><P>Yes if given "admin" rights. </P><P>5. How cooperative will our DM's have to be all on the same server? Will they need to work together often?</P><P>Seems to be up to the GM's. Do they want to let the other GM know whats going on, or talk over handing out that nifty frostbrand +3 at level 8, is it gonna ruin a gm's day if a ring if invisibility enters the game, etc? I sort of pictured it like someone mentioned. One DM may be good at dungeon and traps. Another maybe on quickie side quest in outdoor zones. Another might want to create a complicated city. As with any pen n paper campaign it will be trial and error. We all remember our first crazy monty haul campaigns where everyone was level 55 and killing dieties. Then the following campaigns where you might have went the other directions and slowed leveling and magical items a bit too much.</P><P>6. Can multiple DM's run a scenario simultaneously?</P><P>yes</P><P>7. Does our server have an "overseer" who coordinates everything?</P><P>Dunno</P><P>8. Is NWN the kind of game, like DAoC or EQ, where people are logged in all the time, or will we have to arrange set times to group and hit the dungeons?</P><P>Well in depth planned adventures that take a lot of DM interaction would be weekly good ole D&D sessions. In between could be short side quests, hack n slash dungeons. From what I gather scenarios do not always need a live DM, its just a fun bonus when you get someone behind the DM screen.</P><P>From what I've read of the community there are 2 schools. One wanting a real DM all the time and as close as possible experience to the old D&D table games with 6 close friends. Others want a string of linked worlds with constantly respawning mobs so that they can level as fast as their playing time will allow. I plan to do both. Characters for LOA run servers and another to server hop, level, collect loot and just see what people imaginations have put out there.</P><P>9. Can this be run in windowed mode, so we have access to chat clients like IRC, or is there a chat area inside the game?</P><P>I hope so!</P><P></P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
