        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> ANYthing in ANY module can be a jump-off point for any other module. So the "dungeon created by Stubby" may have 3 portals in it, each taking a player character to some OTHER module or scene within the adventure. </P><P>When I think of a module, I think of a very detailed, LARGE-scale adventure with it's own plot/storyline. Within each module are multiple 'scenes' --- each can be created by various DMs, if wanted. </P><P>Scenes and modules can be linked with OTHER scenes and modules. Sky is the limit.</P><P>Brimstone</P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
