        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Hmmmm, I'm already working on a project, NWNGHA.</P><P><a href="www.nwngha.com" target="_blank">www.nwngha.com</a></P><P>You should be able to do just about anything with NWN, the scripting will be similar to C and C+.</P><P>The current version (the one that they are working on right now will only allow a few select tile sets (no deserts for example).</P><P>The max for a server is 64 people (this has been set in stone), but one could "link" multiple servers togeather allowing more people to be on (just they wouldn't be able to communicate across servers).</P><P>97%-99% of everything in the game is suposed to be alterable by the DM's.</P><P>A DM can take over any charecter they want so as long they have DM access to that area. (if a module is running and they havn't been given DM powers in that module then they can't, it just depends on who you give DM powers where).</P><P>The creature AI is as robust as you want to make it, thus you can give your creatures certain scripts to do certain things or in certain event react a specific way.</P><P>Mainly right now we are working on populating Greyhawk City and the surounds and creating mods and such. Just waiting to see what really can be done with the game when it comes out.</P><P><b>I highly doubt Sun Tsu meant 'on dealy ground fight ... and if you lose reload'.</b><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
